<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="22" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
The new combination is necessary because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1838" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria brevipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Spach, E" journalOrPublisher="Folia Geobotanica" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" refId="B18" refString="Spach, E, 1839. Histoire naturelle des vegetaux. Phanerogames. Tome septieme. 1-538. ." title="Histoire naturelle des vegetaux. Phanerogames. Tome septieme. 1 - 538." year="1839">Spach (1839)</bibRefCitation>
is illegitimate since it included the older name 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Delphinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pictum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Delphinium pictum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. Jabbour" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="F. Jabbour" baseAuthorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Corsica, Majorca, and Sardinia. Its main habitats are open grasslands covering rocky places from 150 up to 600 m above sea level (
<bibRefCitation author="Orellana, M" journalOrPublisher="Folia Geobotanica" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="47 - 63" publicationUrl="doi: 10.1007/s12224–009–9028-y" refId="B17" refString="Orellana, M, Blanche, C, Simon, J, Bosch, M, 2009b. Genetic diversity within and among disjunct populations of the Mediterranean Island endemic Delphinium pictum and D. requienii (Ranunculaceae). Folia Geobotanica 44: 47 - 63, doi: 10.1007/s12224-009-9028-y" title="Genetic diversity within and among disjunct populations of the Mediterranean Island endemic Delphinium pictum and D. requienii (Ranunculaceae)." url="doi: 10.1007/s12224–009–9028-y" volume="44" year="2009 b">Orellana et al. 2009b</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
